                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The handwriting may be assigned to the sixth century A.D., cf. P. Graec. Berol. 45 (525 A.D.) and P. Lugd. Bat. XIX 21 (6th century A.D.). Though written in a quick semicursive hand, the text leaves an elegant impression, not least because of the straightness of the lines and the regularity of the hand. Upper margin is approximately 1.7 cm., left margin varying between 0.5 cm. and 1 cm., and  at the right the writing extends to the edge of the papyrus in lines 1 and 5. At the bottom, line 7 is practically lost as the sheet breaks off between lines 6 and 7, leaving only traces of the writing on line 7.</p>
                  </handDesc>
